description:
Now known as Czech Republic, its time to explore the small region of Bohemia. This was home to two mighty heroes of the Reformation: John Huss and Jerome. Inspired by the work of John Wycliffe, they worked closely together throughout their lives, both continuing the work of the reform. Their legacy spread beyond their home city of Prague and lives on to this very day.
